{{cooknav}}
''This is an automatically generated category. Do not add recipes here by hand.''
These are recipes which use <nowiki>{{recipe summary}}</nowiki> but do not have a cooking time. [[Category:Cookbook utility categories]] __HIDDENCAT__

This chapter deals with the Further Pure 2 Module of the MEI AS/A2 mathematics GCE. It is assumed that readers are familiar with [[../C1 | C1]], [[../C2 | C2]], [[../C3 | C3]], [[../C4 | C4]] and [[../FP1 | FP1]].
==Examination Structure== The exam consists of 4 questions. There are 72 marks available on the paper, with 18 marks for each question. It is split into two sections, Section A and Section B. Section A consists of three questions. Section B contains 1 question on hyperbolic functions The time allowed for the paper is 1 hour 30 minutes. The Investigation of Curves chapter is included in the textbook but there is no longer an option to choose to answer a question on this topic and so section B is just one question on hyperbolic functions. ==Contents== *[[/Advanced Calculus/]] *[[/Polar Co-ordinates/]] *[[/Complex Numbers/]] *[[/Power Series/]] *[[/Matrices/]] *[[/Hyperbolic Functions/]]
__NOTOC__ __NOEDITSECTION__ {{BookCat}}

This chapter is designed to aid students studying AS/A2 Level Mathematics for the New MEI GCE (Maintained under OCR). It ought to comply with the applicable specification for the GCE, available [http://www.ocr.org.uk/download/kd/ocr_10095_kd_l_gce_spec.pdf here] in pdf format from OCR's website. This books aims at the very least to teach the bare minimum information specified in the official specification, but the reader should note that relying on this textbook alone is ill-advised. All readers are '''strongly''' encouraged to make bold additions to these pages, where doing so will improve the book for all/most users. If at any stage you feel that an extra/replacement example would be helpful, please do not hesitate to make the necessary change! __NOTOC__ __NOEDITSECTION__ ==Contents== ===Pure Modules=== ====Core Modules==== *[[/C1 | Core Mathematics 1]] *[[/C2 | Core Mathematics 2]] *[[/C3 | Core Mathematics 3]] *[[/C4 | Core Mathematics 4]] ====Further Pure Modules==== *[[/FP1 | Further Pure 1]] *[[/FP2 | Further Pure 2]] *[[/FP3 | Additional Further Pure 3]]
====Numerical Modules==== *[[/NM | Numerical Methods]] *[[/NC | Numerical Computation]] ===Applied Modules=== ====Differential Equations==== *[[/DE | Differential Equations]] ====Mechanics Modules==== *[[/M1 | Mechanics 1]] *[[/M2 | Mechanics 2]] *[[/M3 | Mechanics 3]] *[[/M4 | Mechanics 4]] ====Statistics Modules==== *[[/S1 | Statistics 1]] *[[/S2 | Statistics 2]] *[[/S3 | Statistics 3]] *[[/S4 | Statistics 4]] ====Decision Modules==== *[[/D1 | Decision 1]] *[[/D2 | Decision 2]] *[[/DC | Decision Computation]]
{{BookCat}}

